                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1176.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>We have information from Haiti that it is currently reported that ammunition is
                    being supplied to revolutionary forces by Dominicans and that a large quantity
                    was received by sailboat from Monte Christi on May 11. Please bring the matter
                    to the attention of the Government and ask that necessary action be taken to
                    prevent further deliveries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
